  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released 03/19/2018 CT 12:20pm CT (18:20 UTC)</p><h2 id=\"id-1.13.12-PAXDevice&quot;FormatError&quot;Recovery\">PAX Device &quot;Format Error&quot; Recovery</h2><p>We have received reports of PAX Devices presenting\u00a0a &quot;format error&quot; when processing a transaction. When this error occurs, the payment is processed but it is not saved on the RepairQ ticket.\u00a0With this update, RepairQ will automatically recover from a format error.</p><p>The format error happens outside of RepairQ's control, and with a format error RepairQ\u00a0does not receive a normal response\u00a0to process. Now when we receive a format error we use Bluefin's APIs to lookup the transaction, and if it is processed we save it onto the RepairQ ticket without any\u00a0manual intervention required.</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
